cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DB 

This paper is about sponsored search optimization, which is a subfield of information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.CL are the most likely categories. The paper also proposes a new framework that uses machine learning techniques to improve the performance of sponsored search, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with data management and storage issues related to sponsored search, which is related to the category of databases (cs.DB).
